\t- **capture turn:** a stop-hook capture observation with new transcript records\n   172\t  and a repository environment snapshot\n   173\t- **provider turn:** a provider-native conversation grouping, such as a user\n   174\t  prompt and the resulting assistant/tool activity\n   175\t\n   176\tCapture turns are the durable agentlog concept. Provider turns are useful for UI\n   177\tgrouping when available, but they are not portable enough to define the storage\n   178\tmodel across agents.\n   179\t\n   180\tStore `previous_turn_key` as a session-wide previous capture turn pointer when\n","tool_name":null,"tool_input":null,"source_record":{"timestamp":"2026-05-20T02:22:08.670Z","type":"response_item","payload":{"type":"function_call_output","call_id":"[REDACTED:entropy]"}}}